  "text": "-2 -Our model features a global R-symmetry that forbids RPV interactions in the superpotential. This symmetry is broken in a hidden sector and communicated to the MSSM through a heavy mediator that gets integrated out to induce effective RPV A-terms for squarks [CITATION_1] . If gauge mediation communicates SUSY breaking to the visible sector, the spectrum will also feature a metastable gravitino LSP that can be a viable dark matter candidate if thermally produced in the early universe.",
